// tls_echo.tg — a TLS echo server and clients in one process (v0.15).
//
// This is `tcp_echo.tg` over TLS. The only differences are at the two
// endpoints: the server `listen_tls`es with a certificate and key, and
// each client `connect_tls`es. The per-connection *handler* code —
// `accept`, `read_line`, `write`, `close` — is byte-identical to the
// plain-TCP version, because `accept` on a TLS listener transparently
// yields an already-encrypted socket.
//
// It runs hermetically offline: the server presents a throwaway
// self-signed certificate (the `TLS_CERT` / `TLS_KEY` constants below,
// for `127.0.0.1`), and each client passes that same certificate as a
// trusted CA so verification succeeds. Embedded as raw strings — `"…"`
// neither interpolates nor escapes, so the PEM newlines pass through.

